; learning-arc.form — the supervision arc made RUNNABLE: a cold Form-native challenger learns from an
; oracle's labels over a stream, and the body watches it reach the oracle. The loop that runs the bricks.
;
; THE ASK:
;   "Sample the 3rd-party models until the Form-native arms reach or exceed them." champion-challenger.fk
;   decides WHO is the authority over a FIXED competition record; predictor-train.fk interns ONE sample;
;   nearest-shape.fk is the classifier. This brick is the LOOP that runs them as a stream from scratch:
;   for each (feature, oracle-label) in time order, the challenger predicts using only PRIOR exemplars,
;   we tally whether it matched, then it learns that frame — and the agreement count IS the learning curve.
;
; THE SHAPE  (runnable: form-stdlib/learning-arc.fk · proven: tests/learning-arc-band.fk -> 127, composing nearest-shape.fk)
;
;   A SAMPLE = (list feature-vector oracle-label) — the feature a list of small-int bins, the label a string.
;   A STREAM = a list of samples in time order. A PROTOTYPE-SET grows as (cons (list label vector) set).
;
;   1. PREDICT   la-predict (feature protos): the challenger's call — nearest-shape over what it has
;                learned; COLD (no exemplars) is an honest "?", never a fabricated guess. The miss on a
;                shape's first appearance is the price of honesty, and the only miss on a learnable oracle.
;   2. LEARN     la-intern (label feature protos): the smallest act — prepend one (label vector) exemplar
;                (nearest-shape's own teaching: learning is adding a prototype, no weights, no epochs).
;   3. FOLD      la-agreements (samples): predict on current protos, tally the hit, THEN learn this frame
;                for the next — single-pass, order-respecting. Replay the stream, the curve is identical.
;   4. WARMED    la-agreements-after (samples k): learn from every frame but only TALLY after the first k
;                (cold-start exemplars are training, not a fair test of what was learned).
;   5. REACHED   la-reached? (samples k wins-needed): the promotion gate — once warmed past k, did the
;                challenger win at least wins-needed frames? `(ge ... wins-needed)`, division-free. When
;                yes, the Form-native arm has reached the oracle and earned the route (model-retire is next).
;
; THE ONE LANE:
;   This measures the challenger's agreement with the oracle as it learns; it does not judge whether the
;   oracle's label is right — that ground-truth is the oracle's job (a 3rd-party model via predictor-
;   sampling, a declared-source, or a trusted in-house reference). Agreement is an EXACT label match;
;   recognition is nearest-shape's exact-bin count — no distance, no float, no ratio. Honest wall
;   (lc-honest-lane): one exemplar per shape recognizes repeats fast in the body's OWN field (this room,
;   voice, motion); it is not a from-scratch beat of whisper/Vision on the open world. The win is the
;   loop closing — the body learning online, on its own stream, with the curve provable three-way.
;
; KIN: champion-challenger.form (the authority gate this feeds) · predictor-sampling.form (the oracle slot)
;   · predictor-train.form (the single-intern step this folds) · nearest-shape.form (the challenger's
;   classifier) · self-grounding-perception.form (earn trust by proven agreement) · model-retire.form
;   (the endgame once reached) · lc-honest-lane.
;
; LINEAGE: champion-challenger named the north star as a record-counting gate; predictor-train named the
;   single intern; this is those made into a running stream — the cold start, the online learn, the warmed
;   measure, and the line where the challenger has earned the route, all in one fold the kernels agree on.
